  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Top, tail and finely dice the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2090.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2090.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2090.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2090.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2090.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and <strong>carrot</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2090.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2090.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2090.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2090.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2090.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the onion and carrots are cooking, peel and finely slice (don't chop!) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>cherry tomatoes </strong>in half</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2090.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2090.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2090.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2090.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2090.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the<strong> pork & beef ragù mince </strong>and cook for 3-4 min further, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong>, <strong>halved cherry tomatoes</strong> and <strong>dried oregano</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until the tomatoes are starting to break down</p><p>Tip: Crush the tomatoes with a wooden spoon as you stir</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2090.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2090.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2090.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2090.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2090.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve the<strong> beef stock mix</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>and<strong> tomato paste</strong> in 150ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Stir in 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span><strong> milk</strong> – this is your<strong> stock</strong></p><p>Once the tomatoes have started to break down, add the <strong>stock</strong> to the pan and cook for 15-20 min or until the sauce has thickened to a rich, bolognese-like consistency – this is your <strong>Bolognese ragù</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2090.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2090.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2090.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2090.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2090.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the Bolognese ragù has been cooking for 5-10 min, add the <strong>pappardelle </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> over a high heat with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook for 10-12 min or until tender with a slight bite (this is known as al denté)</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>pappardelle</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
